Want to match using like and REGEX?
Read this!

LIKE  -- Basic search (can find "starts with A" or "contains test")
REGEX -- Super search (can find "email format" or "phone number format" or "date format")

LIKE
LIKE  -- Case-sensitive
ILIKE -- Case-insensitive
Wildcards:
%     -- Zero or more of ANY character
_     -- Exactly ONE character

Regular Expression
~     -- Matches regex Case-sensitive
~*    -- Matches regex Case-insensitive
!~    -- Does NOT match Case-sensitive
!~*   -- Does NOT match Case-insensitive
Common Regex Patterns:
Pattern   | Meaning                      | Example
^         | Anchors: Start of string     | ^Hello (starts with Hello)
$         | Anchors: End of string       | world$ (ends with world)
.         | Any single character         | a.c matches abc, a1c
*         | Zero or more of previous     | ab*c matches ac, abc, abbc
+         | One or more of previous      | ab+c matches abc, abbc NOT ac
?         | Zero or one of previous      | ab?c matches ac, abc
[abc]     | Any of a, b, or c            | [abc] matches a, b, or c
[a-z]     | Any lowercase letter         | [a-z] matches a to z
[A-Z]     | Any uppercase letter         | [A-Z] matches A to Z
[0-9]     | Any digit                    | [0-9] matches 0 to 9
[^abc]    | NOT a, b, or c               | [^abc] matches any except a, b, c
\d        | Digit (same as [0-9])        | \d\d matches 12, 99
\w        | Word char (a-z, A-Z, 0-9, _) | \w+ matches hello_123
\s        | Whitespace                   | \s matches space, tab, newline
\         | Escape character             | \. literal dot
\.        | Literal period               | \.com matches .com
{a,b}     | Repetition between a and b   | {3} exactly repeat 3 times
`         | `(pipe)                      | '|'
